<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>I am not sure this is worth the effort, but it seems worthy enough to consider.</p>

<p>Shahar and I were chatting about preventing access to unit tests by web servers, in order to minimize unforseen security risks.</p>

<p>For example, we could test for something like $_SERVER['REMOTE_ADDR'] or add a ".htaccess" file to help prevent accidentally executing files in the "tests" directory.</p>

